</P>
<P>
   (NYT34) NEW YORK -- Dec. 31, 1999 -- NEWYEAR-TIMESSQUARE-9 --
Times Square celebrates the arrival of the year 2000 early
Saturday. From the black drizzle of dawn until the pyrotechnic
spectacle of midnight, a mighty crush of New Year's merrymakers
welcomed the year 2000 in Times Square, the world's most famous
intersection. (Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
