<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT (Moved in ``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The century's turn has been a time of retrospectives: what was
the most important event, who was the most influential thinker? The
Times decided to look ahead at what some of today's researchers are
working on. From the most raked-over field, like the history of the
ancient world, to the latest medical technology, scholars are
coming up with fresh insights. Some ideas may turn into
breakthroughs, and others may turn out to be dead ends, but the
journey is rarely boring. Here is a handful of works in progress.:
</P>
<P>
   ATTENTION-DEFICIT (Undated) _ Is Attention Deficit Disorder a
cultural rather than medical condition? By Laurence Zuckerman.
</P>
<P>
   SPARTAN-WOMEN (Undated) _ The women of ancient Sparta were
pretty liberated. By Laurence Zuckerman.
</P>
<P>
   GRAFFITI-CRIME (Undated) _ A study of graffiti in the '70s shows
there is no link with crime. By Dinitia Smith.
</P>
<P>
   EPILEPSY-GUN (Undated) _ A study of how to treat epilepsy with a
gamma gun instead of brain surgery. By Denise Caruso.
</P>
<P>
   AMERICAN-CHARACTER (Undated) _ The American character is based
on the idea of puritan responsibility, not freedom, as has been the
traditional interpretation. By Edward Rothstein.
</P>
<P>
   ELIOT-SPENCER (Undated) _ Herbert Spencer spurned George Eliot,
saying they'd have ugly children. Then she started making fun of
his social Darwinist ideas in her novels. By Barbara Boxer.
</P>
<P>
   CALENDAR-1000 (Undated) _ A calendar from the year 1000 shows
what life was like then. By Joyce Jensen.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OTHER CULTURE AND ENTERTAINMENT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YEAR-IN-POP (Undated) _ What the year's pop hits had to say to
the audience. By Ann Powers.
</P>
<P>
   YULIN-PLAY (Undated) _ Harris Yulin talks about his roles in the
play ``The Price'' and the film ``Cradle Will Rock.'' By Jesse
McKinley.
</P>
<P>
   With photos, NYT1, 2.
</P>
<P>
   ARSONISTS-RAP-REVIEW (New York) _ Arsonists, at SOB's. Reviewed
by Ann Powers.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   AILEY-DANCE-REVIEW (New York) _ Alvin Ailey, ``Polish Pieces,''
``Episodes'' at the City Center. Reviewed by Jennifer Dunning.
</P>
