   Y2K-WHAT-PROBLEM? (Undated) _ Now that the year 2000 has arrived
around the world without significant disruptions of power,
transportation, commerce, and other activities dependent on
computers, the question arises: Was the problem overstated, or was
it all those hundreds of billions of dollars that were spent to fix
things that prevented a catastrophe? By Barnaby J. Feder and Andrew
C. Revkin.
</P>
