 Attn Sports Editors:  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sports stories from The New York Times News Service for Sunday,
Jan. 2, 2000.
</P>
<P>
   LIPSYTE-COLUMN (Undated) _ An overview of the Times' century
package looking into the future: It was not until after the
Players' Riot of 2019, in which hundreds of fans were injured and
two died, that America began to take seriously the possibility that
sports was no national campfire but rather a dangerously
out-of-control brush fire that could consume the entire country. By
Robert Lipsyte.
</P>
<P>
   CENTURY-TEAMS (Undated) _ To review this sports century is to
chronicle sport's amazing growth and celebrate its astonishing
accomplishments. But over the last 10 decades, the sports landscape
is also littered with ignominious moments from defunct teams of
leagues gone by. By David Fischer.
</P>
<P>
   CENTURY-SPORTSWRITERS (Undated) _ Wrapping up the most
influential voices in sports writing in the 20th century. By Ira
Berkow.
</P>
<P>
   ARATON-COLUMN (Undated) _ The year of the tortured coach: Casey,
Fassel, Van Gundy, Muckler, Torre, Valentine. By Harvey Araton.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-FLORIDA-BOWDEN (Gainsville, Fla.) _ Bobby Bowden, Florida's
seventysomething coach, shows no signs of slowing down. By Joe
Drape.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-GIANTS-COWBOYS (Dallas or undated) _ Giants advance for
Cowboys game and the men who may not be Giants next season. Win or
lose this game, what does the season mean to the Giants future. By
Bill Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-RONNIE-LOTT (Undated) _ Ronnie Lott spent nine years with
the San Francisco 49ers, and earned the reputation as one of the
best safeties to ever play the game. Now, Lott says he is hoping to
change the way the football union does business, and is strongly
considering a run to replace its longtime executive director, Gene
Upshaw. By Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-DEVILS-BRUINS (Boston) _ Devils at Boston, 7 p.m. By Alex
Yannis.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ A look back at the early years of Major
League Baseball. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ A former high-flying agent is suing a
former protege, 10 players and Wilhelmina Models of New York,
accusing them of engaging in a scheme to defraud him. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BOAT-AMERICAS-CUP (Auckland, New Zealand) _ A set-up of
America's Cup challenger semifinals, which start Jan.2., and the
first day's racing. By Christopher Clarey.
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS-HUNTING (Kingston, N.Y.) _ Woodcock hunting with an old
man and his dog. By Pete Bodo.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other sports
stories from our partners: The Boston Globe, Cox News Service,
Hearst News Service, The Arizona Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort
Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News, San Francisco
Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
