 &HT;    
 &HT;    
 &HT;    RUSSIA-CHEHNYA (Alkhan-Yurt, Chechnya) _ For the first three
months of their military campaign, Russia made short work of the
militants. Russian forces raced through the northern plains of
Chechnya before seizing the lowlands to the south. Grozny, however,
is different. The sprawling city has turned out to be, once again,
a deadly killing zone.
 &HT;    By Michael R. Gordon.
 &HT;    
 &HT;     c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service  
